                    "company": "Eindhoven University of Technology",
                    "description": "As part of my master Mechanical Engineering, I designed a Multi-beam Optical Stress Sensor. The project was realised as a part of the PhD project of MSc. R.F.M. Martens at the TU/e, under supervision of dr. ir. J.P.M. Hoefnagels. \n\nWithin this project vibration measurements, in the nanometer range, were performed. With these measurements, the design of the MOSS was conceived. This design was subjected to multiple Finite Element Analyses  (FEM) and cross-referenced with the vibrational measurements. Thereafter, the design was altered to better suit the operational environment. \n\nThe final result of the project was rewarded an 8.5/10 score. The completion of this project marks the beginning of my graduation project.",
